The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Mumbai, June 11: India?s foreign exchange (forex) reserves plunged by a massive $1.168 billion for the week ended June 3, hit by the revaluation of international currencies. The reserves now stand at $138.661 billion, according to the Reserve Bank of India?s weekly statistical supplement released here today. India?s forex reserves had increased by $175 million for the week ended May 27, after registering a decline for the previous four weeks. Foreign currency assets also fell by $1,218 million to $1,32,730 million.

 Mumbai, June 11: The Reserve Bank of India is planning to set up a board for laying down codes and standards for the Indian banking industry by November. This would be a governing board to monitor and ensure better compliance of corporate governance standards within the Indian banks, RBI deputy governor V. Leeladhar said. All the members for this board would be appointed outside the RBI. This is to align the regulatory requirements and operational freedom of a company.




